args: Enemies detected in all directions.\nProbability of success: Low.
Sounds like we're surrounded.\nWe'll have to find a way to break\nthrough their lines and escape.
Hee hee! Oh, there's no need for THAT.
A breakthrough point is not something to\nbe foundâ€”it is something you CREATE!
Cleo, you see the force stationed on the\nhill over there, yes? Might you be so\nkind as to attack the crag at their feet?
Just to be clear, you want me to attack\nthe rocks NEAR the soldiers and not the\nsoldiers themselves?
Sha Wujing used to be a tactician back\nin Taiwu, Cleo. He must have a plan.
Though this be madness, I pray\nthere is method in it. ...Yaaah!
Bwaaa ha ha! They can't aim at all!
They're clearly firing in blind desperation.\nWe'll just wait this out and...
The hill collapsed in a landslide, but how?\nMy magic was not nearly powerful enough\nto cause such destruction.
The ground beneath the hill was unsound,\nand the crag was the only thing keeping it\nin place. Without it... Hee hee!
I KNEW you had something planned!\nYou tacticians really are something.

HmmmmMMMMM? Tactician? Oh no,
that was experience gained from my time
as a public servant. Judging soil quality
is the key to flood prevention, after all!
Now then! It appears the landslide has\nsettled, which meeeeans...WE RIDE!

The force on the hill has been wiped out!
The siege is broken; the lines in disarray!
Let us break through the enemy and then
conceal ourselves in the woods!
Don't let 'em get away, you fools! Go!
Enemy forces approaching.\nRequesting permission to intercept.
Wait, my mechanical friend! Wait.\nThe time must be as ripe as the\nmost luscious peach on the tree!
Also, Laxi, you have not yet heard my\nsecret plan! Now, when I give the signal...
They're in the woods somewhere!\nFlush 'em out!

Hee hee! Is that panic in your voice?
Yesssss... Moooore... Give me more!
Feel the doubt! Let fear run over you like
a spider with a thousand hairy legs!
For a soldier with a worn-out spirit\nis a soldier that counts for NOTHING!
THIS is the Tiger Ambush strategy!
GAAAH! WHAT'S THAAAAT?!\nPhew! Just a bird. Okay,\nkeep it together here...
Now! The time is as ripe as the most\nsucculent apple in the bowl! NOOOOW!
Stand your ground! They're off the mark!
Ah, but we are right on target.
Should you reeeeally be looking over there\nwhen the true threat is...ABOVE YOU?!

This? Oh, it's just a little device of mine
that shoots rope arrows. I call it the
Cablebow, and it creates a DELIGHTFUL
place for Laxi to hide in the trees above!
I can't believe we won so handily when\nwe were so terribly outnumbered.
It's all thanks to Sha Wujing's plan.\nWe owe you a great debt.
HmmmMMM? Oh, there's no need to\nthank me. Honestly, it was a delightful\nchance to show the fruits of my research.
Oh my, yes! You see, the moment I saw\nLaxi, I came up with a new military tactic.
It was an effective tactic.\nI would like to try it again.
Nothing pleases me more than seeing\nthe delight in your eyes, Laxi!
And iiiiiin that case...might I trouble you\nfor the teeniest, tiniest of favors?
I just want to disassemâ€” BLARGH!
Restrain yourself, sir! I swear, this man\nis more trouble than he's worth...
